               <p>WILLIAM HENRY WHITEHEAD. I am a <rs id="t18310908-74-viclabel423" type="occupation">solicitor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-74-victim691 t18310908-74-viclabel423"></join>. I was in the narrow passage leading from <placeName id="t18310908-74-crimeloc424">Lincoln's Inn New-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-74-crimeloc424" type="placeName" value="Lincoln's Inn New-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-74-crimeloc424" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-74-off421 t18310908-74-crimeloc424"></join>, to <placeName id="t18310908-74-crimeloc425">Serle-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-74-crimeloc425" type="placeName" value="Serle-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-74-crimeloc425" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-74-off421 t18310908-74-crimeloc425"></join>, about a quarter before three o'clock in the afternoon of the 4th of July; my nephew, who was with me, told me my handkerchief was taken -I turned and found it on the ground in a corner, where it could not have dropped; it had been in my pocket - the prisoner, who was close behind me, was pointed out, and I called an officer.</p>

               <p>JOHN 
               <persName id="t18310908-74-person692">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  BEGBEE
               <interp inst="t18310908-74-person692" type="surname" value="BEGBEE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-74-person692" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-74-person692" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was walking a little behind my uncle, and saw the prisoner put his hand into the pocket and pull the handkerchief out; I told my uncle immediately - the prisoner put the handkerchief into his pocket, but when I told my uncle he took it out, and threw it on the ground.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking in the passage - there were several persons there; a person tapped me on the shoulder and said, I had picked that gentleman's pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-74-verdict426" type="verdictDescription">
